          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":52,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"18–20 km at easy pace (5:22–5:56/km). This is your aerobic anchor for the week — keep it conversational and relaxed. No pressure to push the back half.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day after your long run. Let the adaptation begin — recovery is where fitness is actually built.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10–11 km easy (5:22–5:56/km). Shake out the legs from Sunday. If you feel sluggish, that's completely normal — just stay in the easy zone.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"10 km total with 4 km at threshold pace (4:28/km). Warm up 3 km easy, 4 km tempo, cool down 3 km easy. This sustains your lactate threshold and keeps that hard-earned fitness sharp.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10 km easy (5:22–5:56/km). A steady aerobic day to accumulate volume without adding stress. Keep it genuinely easy.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or very light movement (walking, stretching). You've earned it — Friday rest sets you up well for a quality Saturday.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10–11 km easy (5:22–5:56/km). Optional strides (4×100m at repetition effort, 4:00/km feel) at the end if legs feel fresh — these maintain neuromuscular sharpness without adding meaningful fatigue.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to your maintenance plan, Maria. Week 1 is intentionally dialed back to around 52 km — a deliberate step down from your recent 63–64 km weeks. Think of this as setting the foundation rhythm rather than backing off. Your recent training history shows you've been putting in serious work, and maintenance isn't about coasting — it's about sustaining the fitness you've built with a smarter, more sustainable load. The focus this week is aerobic volume (easy runs), one quality threshold session to keep your lactate fitness tuned, and two proper rest days. Given your history of left Achilles tendinitis, we're keeping easy days genuinely easy and building mindful recovery into the structure. Your VDOT of 46.7 reflects real fitness — let's protect and preserve it.\"}"
        }
      ]
